      "avalancheActivity": {
        "comment": "The avalanche risk is considerable at higher altitudes and moderate below. In steep terrain, especially in the northern and shaded areas, slab avalanches can be triggered by even a small additional load. There are avalanche prone locations, for example at terrain transitions and transitions from more to less snow. Depending on the altitude and aspect, spontaneous slab avalanches or wet snow avalanches must be taken into account. They mainly reach medium size, but can also tear through to the ground and therefore become somewhat larger.",
        "highlights": "Slab avalanches can still be triggered easily and naturally triggered avalanches must be observed!"
      },
